    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint: non-cannulated pedicle screw, ASTM F1717, static loading only",
      "description": "Model predictions are applicable exclusively to non-cannulated titanium alloy pedicle screws with nominal outer diameter 7.5 mm and thread pitch 2.75 mm, tested under quasi-static ASTM F1717 compression-bending protocol at room temperature (20–25 °C). Application to cannulated designs, dynamic fatigue loading, in vivo bone anchorage, or screws outside the 6.5–8.5 mm diameter range is outside scope and requires separate validation."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "Operating envelope: ASTM F1717 static compression-bending test boundary conditions",
      "description": "The validated operating envelope spans: axial compressive load 0–3500 N applied at 5 mm/min crosshead displacement rate; construct offset distance 40 mm per ASTM F1717 fixture geometry; rod diameter 5.5 mm cobalt-chrome; pedicle screw insertion angle 0° (perpendicular to rod axis); ambient temperature 20–25 °C; relative humidity 30–70 %. Material properties are bounded by Ti-6Al-4V ELI (elastic modulus 110–114 GPa, yield strength 795–900 MPa). Extrapolation beyond these bounds is not supported by the validation evidence."
    }
  },
  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/sensitivity/cou1-noncannulated",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sensitivity analysis: material property and contact friction variation on predicted QoIs",
    "description": "A one-at-a-time sensitivity study varied Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (±5 GPa around 113 GPa), yield strength (±50 MPa around 860 MPa), and screw-rod contact friction coefficient (0.1–0.4) across the full FEA ensemble. Construct stiffness showed less than 3% variation to material property perturbations and less than 7% variation to friction coefficient changes, while yield force was most sensitive to yield strength (6.2% range) and least sensitive to friction (1.8% range), confirming that material property uncertainty is the dominant contributor to model output variability and that the adopted uncertainty quantification bounds are conservative."
  },
